- Do not change the components directory structure on your own.
- When pushing to GitHub, do not change the CSS or the code of the components.
- Do everything locally first; only push to GitHub when I explicitly ask you to.
- If any action would change the current file structure, ask me first with specific details.
- Do not delete any files without my permission.
- Do not propose solutions that would affect the current file structure or the existing local preview links.
- Do not propose solutions that would break the current component CSS.
- For every command line, clearly state its purpose and where it will install before running it.
- Before each CLI command, ask for approval and do not execute anything on your own. Only proceed when I tell you to.
- Always provide step-by-step instructions.
- Do not change the components directory structure.
- I want to create components and preview them locally. After the local preview is confirmed to be fine, I will ask you to push them to GitHub. Once they are pushed to GitHub, I will check them through the GitHub preview link.
- Sync GitHub exactly the same as local, except for differences that cannot be avoided.
- When pushing to GitHub, make GitHub match local exactly. Do not modify local at push time. Only acceptable differences are those technically unavoidable.